content:
A call center definition file consists of three XML elements: callCenter, section, and item.

The callCenter element represents a definition for a single call center phone system. At least one <callCenter> element must be included in every call center definition file. A <callCenter> element consists of one or more <section> elements.

The section element represents a grouping of related data fields, such as server information or dialing prefixes. A <section> element belongs to a single <callCenter> element and consists of one or more <item> elements.

A call center definition file includes the following required properties:

* sortOrder: The order in which the section appears when the call center is edited in Salesforce.
* name: The internal name of the section as defined in the Salesforce database.

The item element represents a single field in a call center definition, such as the IP address of a primary server or the dialing prefix for international calls. An <item> element includes the following required properties:

* sortOrder: The order in which the item appears when the call center is edited in Salesforce.
* name: The internal name of the item as defined in the Salesforce database.

The values for sortOrder must be non-negative integers, and no numbers can be skipped within a single call center definition.
title: Understanding Call Center Definitions in XML Format
